Preheat the oven to 200C/180C Fan/Gas6.Place the vegetables and garlic in a roasting tin.Mix the oil with the herbs and seasoning, and the lemon juice if using.Pour over the vegetables and toss thoroughly. Place in the preheated oven and bake for 30-40 minutes until the vegetables are tender and well browned, this may only take 20-25 minutes if using pre-roasted frozen vegetables.Place in a saucepan with the vegetable stock. Bring to the boil and then simmer for 5 minutes. Cool.Blend half of the mixture, then return to the pan to reheat.Serve with crusty bread.